    "excerpt": "As part of our ongoing commitment to community resilience, psychosocial support, and dignity restoration, the Coalition for Community Resilience and Transformation (CArCRT) has initiated a strategic collaboration with the Sierra Leone Correctional Service, Kenema. This partnership aims to strengthen rehabilitation pathways and improve support systems for inmates through our new initiative titled Project Closed Setting.",
    "content": "CArCRT Partners with Sierra Leone Correctional Service to Launch “Project Closed Setting”\r\n\r\nAs part of our ongoing commitment to community resilience, psychosocial support, and dignity restoration, the Coalition for Community Resilience and Transformation (CArCRT) has initiated a strategic collaboration with the Sierra Leone Correctional Service, Kenema. This partnership aims to strengthen rehabilitation pathways and improve support systems for inmates through our new initiative titled Project Closed Setting.\r\n\r\nAbout the Project\r\n\r\nProject Closed Setting focuses on providing holistic rehabilitation and reintegration support for inmates through:\r\n\r\n1. Psychosocial Support & Counseling\r\n\r\nIndividual and group counseling sessions\r\n\r\nTrauma healing and emotional recovery\r\n\r\nMentorship programs to rebuild confidence, resilience, and hope\r\n\r\n2. Skills Training & Entrepreneurship\r\n\r\nPractical vocational training\r\n\r\nEntrepreneurship and business development skills\r\n\r\nOpportunities to prepare inmates for sustainable livelihoods post-release\r\n\r\n3. Dignity Support for Women\r\n\r\nTailored programs for female inmates\r\n\r\nHygiene and dignity kits\r\n\r\nEmpowerment sessions aimed at reducing stigma and restoring self-worth\r\n\r\n4. Reintegration & Safe Life After Prison\r\n\r\nStructured reintegration planning\r\n\r\nCommunity mentorship and referral pathways\r\n\r\nAgribusiness and livelihood opportunities to support a smooth transition back into society\r\n\r\nOur Commitment\r\n\r\nThrough this partnership, CArCRT continues to champion inclusive rehabilitation, promote human dignity, and support second chances for individuals in closed settings. We believe that every person—regardless of circumstance—deserves access to healing, growth, and the opportunity to rebuild their lives.",
